---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Two Wheeler Loan - Bike & Scooter Finance at Low EMIs | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Two Wheeler Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Two Wheeler Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Finance your dream bike or scooter with two wheeler loans at interest rates starting from 7.99% p.a. Get up to 100% on-road price financing with flexible EMIs and tenure up to 5 years. Quick approval for all major brands.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹20K - ₹10L</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: 6 Months - 5 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 7.99% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Two Wheeler Loan?</h2>
          <p>A two wheeler loan is a secured vehicle loan that helps you purchase a new or used motorcycle, scooter, or moped by financing up to 85-100% of the on-road price. The vehicle itself serves as collateral, which is why interest rates are lower than personal loans. Two wheeler loans are available for all major brands including Honda, Hero, TVS, Bajaj, Royal Enfield, Yamaha, Suzuki, and electric two wheelers from Ola, Ather, and TVS iQube.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert partners with over 25 banks, NBFCs, and manufacturer financing arms to bring you the best two wheeler loan deals. Whether you're buying a budget commuter scooter for ₹70,000 or a premium superbike for ₹10 lakhs, we have financing options for every budget. Our platform also offers special zero down payment schemes, cashback offers, and reduced processing fee deals during festive seasons.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">7.99%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">100%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Financing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">5 Years</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Two Wheeler Loan Interest Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>7.99% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finance</td>
                <td>8.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>9.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Hero FinCorp</td>
                <td>8.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Manappuram Finance</td>
                <td>10.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Indian citizen aged between 18 and 65 years (21 for some lenders)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹8,000 for salaried or regular income for self-employed</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Valid driving license for two wheeler (or to be obtained before delivery)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 650 or above (some lenders accept lower scores with higher interest)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum 6 months in current employment or 1 year of self-employment</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Valid ID and address proof with residence stability of at least 1 year</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get a Two Wheeler Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Choose Your Vehicle</h4>
              <p>Select the bike or scooter you want. Check the on-road price including registration, insurance, and accessories.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Check EMI Options</h4>
              <p>Use our EMI calculator to plan your budget. Compare loan offers from 25+ lenders for the best rate and tenure combination.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Apply at Dealership</h4>
              <p>Apply through TrueCred or directly at the dealership. Most two wheeler loans are approved within 30 minutes to 2 hours.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Ride Home</h4>
              <p>Loan disbursed directly to the dealer. Complete registration formalities and ride home on your new two wheeler the same day.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Identity Proof — Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Voter ID, or Passport</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Address Proof — Aadhaar, Utility Bill, or Passport with current address</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income Proof — Latest 2-3 months salary slips or 6 months bank statements</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Bank Statements — Last 3 months for salaried, 6 months for self-employed</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Vehicle quotation — Proforma invoice from the authorized dealership</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies) and cancelled cheque</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for Two Wheeler Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="20000">₹20,000</option>
                  <option value="40000">₹40,000</option>
                  <option value="60000">₹60,000</option>
                  <option value="80000">₹80,000</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="150000">₹1,50,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about two wheeler loans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a two wheeler loan with zero down payment?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, several lenders offer 100% on-road price financing, effectively giving you a zero down payment loan. HDFC Bank and Bajaj Finance regularly run zero DP schemes during festive seasons. However, keep in mind that higher financing means higher EMIs and total interest cost. Making a 10-20% down payment can significantly reduce your monthly outgo and help you get a lower interest rate.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the EMI for a ₹1 lakh two wheeler loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              For a ₹1 lakh two wheeler loan at 8.5% interest rate: EMI for 1 year is approximately ₹8,720, for 2 years is ₹4,560, for 3 years is ₹3,160, and for 4 years is ₹2,460. Longer tenure means lower EMIs but higher total interest paid. Use our EMI calculator to plan the exact amount based on the rate offered to you.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a loan for a used/second-hand two wheeler?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, several NBFCs and fintech lenders offer loans for used two wheelers, though with some restrictions: the vehicle should typically be less than 5 years old, financing is usually up to 50-70% of the current market value, interest rates are 2-3% higher than new vehicle loans, and the loan tenure is shorter (up to 3 years). Bajaj Finance and Manappuram are active in the used two wheeler loan segment.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I prepay or foreclose my two wheeler loan early?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, you can prepay or foreclose your two wheeler loan after the lock-in period (usually 6 months to 1 year). Foreclosure charges range from 2-5% of the outstanding principal. Some lenders waive foreclosure charges after a certain period or number of EMIs. Prepaying your loan early saves significantly on interest — always check the prepayment terms before taking the loan.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Do I need insurance for a two wheeler loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, comprehensive motor insurance is mandatory for two wheeler loans. The vehicle must be insured for the full loan tenure, and the insurance policy must include the lender as a hypothecation holder. If you let the insurance lapse, the lender may impose penalties. First-year insurance is usually bundled with the vehicle purchase, but remember to renew it annually throughout the loan tenure.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Ride Your Dream Bike Home Today</h3>
          <p>Up to 100% financing on all bike and scooter brands. EMIs starting from ₹1,999. Apply in 2 minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
